# Market Analysis

Guidelines for market research, segmentation, competitive analysis, and sizing.

## Research Methodology

```text
Market Research Process
├── Secondary Research (Desk Research)
│   ├── Industry reports (Gartner, Forrester, IDC)
│   ├── Public filings and financial data
│   ├── News and trade publications
│   ├── Government and census data
│   └── Academic papers and whitepapers
├── Primary Research (Field Research)
│   ├── Customer interviews (qualitative)
│   ├── Surveys (quantitative)
│   ├── Focus groups
│   ├── Win/loss analysis
│   └── Ethnographic observation
├── Competitive Intelligence
│   ├── Product teardowns and feature comparison
│   ├── Pricing analysis
│   ├── Positioning and messaging audit
│   ├── Hiring pattern analysis
│   └── Technology stack analysis
└── Data Synthesis
    ├── Pattern identification
    ├── Segment definition
    ├── Opportunity sizing
    └── Strategic recommendations
```

## Segmentation Framework

| Step | Activity | Output |
|------|----------|--------|
| Define variables | Choose segmentation dimensions (firmographic, behavioral, needs-based) | Variable list with definitions |
| Collect data | Gather data on potential customers across variables | Customer dataset |
| Cluster analysis | Group customers with similar profiles | Segment definitions |
| Profile segments | Describe each segment's characteristics, size, and needs | Segment profiles |
| Evaluate segments | Score attractiveness: size, growth, accessibility, fit | Prioritized segment list |
| Select targets | Choose segments to pursue based on strategy | Target segment decisions |

### Segment Evaluation Criteria

| Criterion | Weight | Description |
|-----------|--------|------------|
| Market size | 20% | Revenue potential of the segment |
| Growth rate | 15% | Year-over-year segment growth |
| Competitive intensity | 15% | Number and strength of competitors serving this segment |
| Accessibility | 15% | Ability to reach and serve the segment with current resources |
| Strategic fit | 15% | Alignment with company capabilities and vision |
| Willingness to pay | 10% | Price sensitivity and budget availability |
| Switching costs | 10% | Barriers to leaving current solution |

## Market Sizing Methods

| Method | Approach | Best For |
|--------|---------|----------|
| Top-Down | Start with total market, apply filters | TAM estimation, investor presentations |
| Bottom-Up | Start with unit economics, multiply by reachable customers | SOM estimation, revenue planning |
| Value Theory | Estimate total value delivered, capture percentage | New categories with no existing market data |
| Analog | Use comparable market as proxy | Emerging markets with limited data |

